Commentary: Boult starts with a good length ball outside off, there is a hint of away swing on this one. Karunaratne leaves it alone to start off his innings.
Hits the deck hard on off, there is hardly any movement on this one. Dimuth gets behind the ball and defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the front foot.
On the fourth stump line, Karunaratne does not disturb that.
Once again Boult tempts Dimuth to drive but Karunaratne does not fall into the trap.
Outside off, Dimuth leaves it alone to get through the over. Maiden to begin with for New Zealand.
Southee starts with a good length ball on off, Thirimanne begins his innings with a solid back foot defense.
On top of off, Thirimanne gets behind the ball and keeps it out.
Southee continues to bowl in the channel of off stump. Thirimanne keeps his focus and blocks it.
Southee misses his line and bowls one down the leg side. Lahiru goes for the flick but misses. BJ Watling behind the stumps, dives to his right and does well to save runs for his side.
Back of a length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it with a straight bat.
Maiden for Southee too to begin with. Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne leaves it alone. Sri Lanka yet to get off the mark.

FOUR! Sri Lanka are underway! Length ball around off, Karunaratne picks the length early and punches it wide of point. The fielder at point dives to his right but cannot stop the ball. The ball beats him and races away to the fence.
Follows it up with a calm and sensible leave outside off.

EDGED AND FOUR! Boult bowls an away swinger pitching on off, Karunaratne looks to defend but ends up edging it. He though plays it with soft hands, meaning that even though the ball takes the outside edge it goes all along the ground, between gully and point for a boundary.
Now calmly defends it right off the meat towards cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Dimuth keeps it out.
Outside off, Karunaratne has nothing to do with it and leaves it alone. 8 off the over.
Southee bowls it on the pads, Thirimanne looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the keeper.
On a length on middle, Thirimanne flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Back of a length ball on off and middle, Karunaratne keeps his eyes on the ball and pulls it in a controlled manner through mid-wicket for a couple.
Length ball outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on off, Dimuth keeps it out.
On the 4th stump line, Karunaratne has no business with it.
Good length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it right of the middle.
On top of off, Lahiru blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery on off, Thirimanne gets on his back foot and blocks it.
Good length ball outside off, it nips back in but Thirimanne is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.
No swing on this one as this starts on the 4th stump line and goes straight to the keeper.
Length ball on middle, Thirimanne blocks it off the front foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Another edge from Karunaratne which goes between second slip and gully. Fuller on off, Dimuth looks to defend with soft hands. The ball zips away and takes the fat outside edge of Karunaratne's bat. It dissects slip and gully and races away to the fence.
Hits the deck outside off, it comes in but Karunaratne shows his calm and awareness and leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Another calm leave from Karunaratne outside his off pole.
Fuller on middle and off, Dimuth flicks it but finds mid-wicket.

Ohh! Length ball outside off, Dimuth initially looks to play but then decides to leave in the last minute. He is late though as the ball hits the lower half of his bat. Luckily for him there is no casualty.
On the pads, Thirimanne looks to flick but the ball goes off his pad fine down the leg side. The batsmen take a single as BJ Watling cleans it up.
Non swinger outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
Length ball on top of off, Dimuth defends it off the back foot towards point.

Just a bit too high. Good length ball pitching on off, Karunaratne strides forward to defend but the ball nips in sharply. Dimuth misses his defense and the ball hits him high on the pads. There is a huge appeal but nothing form the umpire.
FOUR! Crunched away! This is how you respond to an LBW call. Good length ball outside off,  Karunaratne picks it early and slams it over the point fielder for a boundary.
On off, Karunaratne defends it to get through the over.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Very full on middle, Lahiru does well to get his bat down in time and keep it out.
Length delivery closer to the off pole, Thirimanne taps it towards gully.
Play and a miss! Southee bowls it full outside off, Thirimanne's eyes lit up looking at the line outside off. Lahiru goes for the drive but luckily does not get a feather on it to the keeper.
Full on middle, LT defends it off the middle of his bat towards mid on.
Away swinger full on off, Dimuth gets right behind the ball and defends it solidly towards mid off.
Good length ball around off, Karunaratne keeps it out of his back foot.
Fuller on off, Dimuth shows that he is in good form as once again he defends it right off the middle of his willow.
Outside off, Karunaratne will hardly ever go after that one. He shoulders arms to it in a typical Test match fashion.
Good length ball on off, the Sri Lankan skipper defends it towards mid on.

Full on off and middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket. The outfield was covered so it is not as slow as it would have been in other parts of the world. The ball still does not have the legs to reach the fence. The fielder cleans it up. The batters meanwhile come back for the third.
Fuller outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.
Shorter around the body, first short ball this. Karunaratne ducks under it.
Length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it with a straight bat.
Fuller and going away with the angle, Karunaratne defends it with the angle towards cover.
Full ball outside off, DK shoulders arms to one more ball that is outside off. Classical Test match batting.
Length delivery on middle, Thirimanne flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.

Good fielding! Back of a length ball around off, Karunaratne hops and guides it through third man. Nicholls and Williamson go after it. Nicholls dives and pulls it before the ropes. He lays it behind to Williamson. Saves a run for his side.
Fuller on middle, Thirimanne strokes it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot.
On middle and leg, Lahiru tucks it towards square leg.
Starts with a good length ball on off and middle, Dimuth defends it towards mid-wicket.
On a length outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Outside off, Dimuth punches it off the inner half of his bat towards point.
On middle, Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.

Direct hit but no issue. Good length ball around off, Karunaratne strokes it towards point and takes a single. The fielder then scores a direct hit at the keeper's end. The ball ricochets off the stumps and goes behind allowing them to take one more.
Dot to finish the over. Length delivery outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to it.
Floated on middle and off, Thirimanne strokes it to mid off.
Flighted on off, Lahiru defends it off the front foot.

DROPPED! Tough chance but Thirimanne has got a lifeline here. Short and spins away just a bit. Thirimanne looks to cut but the ball stays low and kisses the inside edge of the bat. It hits BJ Watling's glove but he fails to take it.
Floated on off, Lahiru keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Thirimanne defends it with a straight bat.
Floated around off, Lahiru blocks it away.

Edged but falls short. Good length ball on off, Dimuth looks to defend but the ball shapes away and takes the outside edge. It falls short off the man at first slip. Just before this ball de Grandhomme wanted Taylor to come a little more further.
Outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Full on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Dimuth punches it to cover-point.
Karunaratne has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller on off, Dimuth taps it back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Thirimanne pushes it to mid off.
Short and spinning away, Thirimanne strokes it with the spin towards point.
Short again on off, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot.

OUT! Caught! Soft dismissal for Thirimanne. Similiar to the way Dimuth got out in the first innings of the first Test. Somerville tosses it up on off, the ball comes slower than Thirimanne expected. He is early in his push and he ends up chipping it straight to cover. New Zealand skipper, Kane Williamson there takes a simple catch. 35 balls for just 2 runs for Thirimanne. All that patience, a dropped catch but for nothing.
Floated on off, Mendis starts his innings off the front foot.
Flighted on off, Mendis bends his back and keeps it out.
Length ball outside off, Karunaratne cuts it through point for a single.
Good length ball outside off, it swings away just a bit. Mendis reads it and leaves it alone.
Fuller on middle, Mendis flicks to mid-wicket.
Full again on middle and leg, Kusal defends it to mid on.

Edged but safe! Also very well stopped by Southee. Good length ball around off, Mendis looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge of Kusal's willow. It goes on a bounce to the right of Southee at second slip. Tim dives and does really well to save runs for his side.
Back of a length ball on off, Mendis keeps it out to get through the over.
Flighted delivery on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Karunaratne drives it to mid off.
Floated delivery on off, the skipper keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards short leg.
Tossed up delivery on off, Karunaratne blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth drives it back towards the bowler.
Fuller on off, Mendis looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge towards cover.
Good length ball on off, Kusal looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge which goes on a bounce towards slip.
Outside off and this time Mendis calmly leaves it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball swinging away from the batter. Mendis looks to defend but once again gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes between slip and gully and to the fence. Kusal continues to struggle with getting proper timing.
Now calmly leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Mendis keeps it out.
FOUR! Smart batting this from the Sri Lankan skipper. Short and spinning away. Dimuth waits and then opens his face of the bat towards the third man region for a boundary.
Follows it up with a calm front foot defense.
Flighted on the stumps, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Karunaratne comes down the track and milks it towards long on for one.
Short and turning in to the batter. Mendis gets on his back foot and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Floats one on off, Karunaratne taps it back towards Somerville.
Fuller on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on off, Mendis strokes it towards mid off. The fielder there dives to his right and saves a certain boundary.
Outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Misfield! Full on middle and off, Kusal strokes it to the right of mid on. Jeet Raval there moves to that side but cannot get down in time. The ball goes past him allowing them to take couple.
On middle, Mendis flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short outside off, Dimuth cuts it against the spin towards point for one.
Shorter on the pads, Kusal tucks it behind square on the leg side.
On the pads, Mendis flicks it to the on side for a single.
Flighted on off, Karunaratne pushes it to cover for a run.

FOUR! Short and rightfully punished. It is on the leg side, a rare loose delivery from Somerville. Mendis is not gonna miss out on that. He gets on his back foot and swivels it to pull through the vacant square leg region for a boundary.
Follows it up with a calm defense to get through the over.
Starts his new spell with a good length ball outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
One more delivery outside off. This is closer to the off pole but Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
On the fourth stump line, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Full outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms to it.
Full around off, Karunaratne drives it off the inner half of his bat straight to mid on.
The line and length is the same but this time Karunaratne drives it to mid off.
Shorter on middle, Mendis tucks it to square leg.
Flights one on off, Kusal bends his back and blocks it.
Short around off, Mendis waits for it and then runs it down towards backward point. The fielder from deep point cleans it up. Two taken. That also brings up the 50 for Sri Lanka.

FOUR! Uppish but just wide. Short on middle and leg, Mendis goes on his back foot and initially looks to sweep. He sees the ball is short so he pulls it wide of backward square leg for a boundary. The fielder dived but had no chance.
Floated on off, Mendis keeps it out.
Once again short, Mendis pulls it towards square leg and keeps the strike.
Good length ball on off and middle, Mendis glances it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Beauty! Southee steams in and pitches it around off. Mendis looks to defend but the ball zips back in viciously. It cuts Mendis in half and just about misses the off pole.
Mendis continues to find the gaps here. Length ball around off, Kusal cuts it through point and gets a couple.
Good length ball on off, Mendis defends it towards point and calls for a single. Dimuth though is quick to refuse it and rightfully so as that would have been nothing but just a suicidal run.
Good length delivery on off, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Mendis lets it carry to the keeper.
Starts with a flighted delivery on off. Karunaratne comes down the track and strokes it wide of mid on for one.
Short on middle. Mendis picks the length early and pulls it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Floated on off, Mendis lunges forward and blocks it.
Tossed up outside off, Mendis strokes it towards cover.
Loopy full toss outside off, Mendis misses out on it as he hits it straight to cover.
On off, Kusal blocks to get through the over.
Length ball around off, Mendis tucks it towards mid-wicket off the inner half of his bat for a run.
Fuller on off, Mendis defends it with a straight bat.
On the stumps, Kusal defends it towards mid on off the inner half of his bat.
Full on off, Mendis drives it to the left of Southee. He puts his left hand out but cannot keep it cleanly as the ball goes to mid off.

Lethargic from Watling. Good length ball outside off, Mendis leaves it alone. Watling loses his concentration and fails to take it. The ball deflects off his gloves away from the slip. Allowing them to take a bye.
Back of a length ball on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Mendis keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Mendis defends it off his front foot.
On off, Mendis blocks it out.
No spin yet for Ajaz. He tosses it up on off, Kusal keeps it out.
FOUR! Comical effort from Raval. Shorter on off, Mendis punches it through cover-point. Raval goes chasing after it and looks to pull it back but he tumbles and the ball races away to the fence.
Follows the boundary with a solid block.
Very well controlled pull this from Karunaratne. Back of a length ball around off, Dimuth pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball on off, Kusal keeps it out.
Outside off, KM leaves it alone.
Good length ball around off, Kusal taps it to gully.
Full on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
On middle, Kusal glances it to the on side and keeps the strike.
Floats one on off, Mendis defends it classically.
Tossed up on middle, Kusal keeps it out.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it to get through the over.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it.
Shorter on off, Kusal punches it to cover.
Loopy ball on off, Mendis strokes it back towards the bowler to get through the over and the 1st session of the day.
FOUR! Sri Lanka are back for the new session with a bang! Overpitched ball around off, Dimuth gets on his front foot and creams his drive through extra cover for a boundary.
Now calmly leaves this one alone outside off.
Good length ball on the 4th stump line, Karunaratne has no business with it.
Tempting Karunaratne to drive by bowling outside off. Dimuth is having none of it.
Away from the off pole, DK shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on the 5th stump line.  DK lets it carry to the keeper.
Starts his new spell with a fuller ball outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
On off and middle this time, Kusal defends it towards cover.
Full on off, Kusal looks to defend but it goes to the on side off the inner half of his defensive bat.
Pulls his length back and bowls outside off, Mendis punches it towards sweeper cover and gets to the other end. His first run of this session.
Full on off, Dimuth pushes it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it off his back foot to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Mendis tucks it to mid-wicket for one.

Safely in!  Brings up the 50-run stand between the two with some hiccup. Good length ball on the pads, Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg and calls for two. They run the first one hard and go for the second. The fielder gets to the ball quickly and sends it to the bowler's end. Southee takes the bails off and the umpire takes it upstairs. One replay is enough to confirm that Kusal Mendis is well in.
Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
On off, Karunaratne punches it to cover.
Length delivery around off, Mendis defends it towards point and shouts a loud no.
Good length ball on off, Mendis defends it to mid off.

OUT! Caught! Colin de Grandhomme breaks the 50-run stand. A gentle delivery just outside off, it moves away just a hint. Moves enough to trouble the batter. Kusal Mendis is drawn forward to defend but not completely committed to the cause. He still goes ahead with it and gets a thin outside edge straight to the keeper. Watling takes a sitter and once again Mendis fails to make the use of his start.
Full on off, Mathews starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Good length ball outside off, Mathews watches it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Mathews blocks it off the front foot. End of a good over from Southee. A wicket maiden.
A short ball, around middle, Karunaratne swivels and pulls it through square leg where the fielder fumbles but recovers quickly. Just a single.
Around off, solidly defended back to the bowler.
Another watchful shot, this time leaving the ball to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Mathews shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Landed outside off, well kept out.
Landed outside off, punched straight to cover.
Landed outside off, steered towards third man. William Somerville gives it a good chase from backward point and slides to his right to stop the ball. Two runs taken.
Outside off, Karunaratne looks to punch it through the off side but gets a thick inside edge which goes past the stumps towards square leg. A single taken.
Full and straight, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball outside off, moving away off the deck, Angelo defends watchfully.
Good length ball around off, Karunaratne defends it to cover.
Length ball around off, Dimuth looks to defend it with soft hands but ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes to the left of first slip. The fielder there dives and saves runs for his team.
This time defends it right of the middle.
On the pads, Dimuth nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good bowling this. Pitches it on middle and makes the ball to tail in. Mathews looks to flick but gets a leading edge which goes all along the ground towards point.
On the pads, Mathews looks to flick but once again misses. This one hits him high on the thigh pad.
Full on off, Dimuth pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Karunaratne runs it down to third man for a single.
Full and swinging away. Mathews pushes it off the inner half of his bat towards mid off.
Starts the new day with a fuller ball on off. Angelo gets on his front foot and pushes it to cover.
Pulls his length back just a hint and bowls it outside off. Angelo leaves it alone.
No ball! Seldom you see a medium pacer overstep. It is full on middle, Mathews blocks it towards mid on.

Mathews is off the mark. It has taken him 18 balls to get the scoreboard ticking. It is on the pads, Mathews glances it towards fine leg and keeps the strike with a single. End of an over which technically lasted more than 8 hours.
Starts with a back of a length ball on off, Mathews defends it off his back foot.
Good length ball pitching on off. It moves away just a hint. Mathews prods forward to defend it with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to second slip on a bounce.
Once again bowls it on a length around off, Mathews punches it to cover.
Maintains the same line and length. Mathews defends it with a straight bat.
Fuller this time on off. Angelo pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, it tails in a bit. Dimuth plants his front foot forward and looks to defend but the ball takes an inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, Dimuth is in no hurry to get to his fifty and leaves it alone.

FIFTY FOR KARUNARATNE. His 23rd in Test cricket. The skipper continues his good form and once again leads his troops from the front. In testing conditions, Dimuth chose to bat and he is paving the path for his teammates to follow. He gets to the milestone by tapping this length ball towards the backward point region and getting to the other end. He raises his bat in appreciation and soaks in all the well deserved applause.
On the fourth stump line, Angelo shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Hits the deck hard on off, Angelo keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller on the stumps, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off and middle, Dimuth strokes it to cover-point.
Full on off, Karunaratne nudges it to mid on as the bat turns in his hand.
Full on off, Dimuth looks to drive but it goes to cover off the outer half of his bat.
Back of a length ball around off, Dimuth punches it towards cover and keeps the strike.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne defends it off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
Full on off, Karunaratne drives it to the right of cover. Southee dives and deflects the ball. Latham behind gets wrong-footed due to the deflection allowing the batsman to take two.
Outside off, Dimuth has no business with it.
Fuller around off once again, Karunaratne drives it towards  point and gets to the other end.
Fuller ball around off, Mathews looks to drive but it zips away a tad and goes off the leading edge towards point for one.
Fuller on middle, Karunaratne defends it properly from the middle of his bat.

OUT! Caught! 250th Test wicket for Trent Boult. This was not the best of balls that Boult has bowled but he will take it with both hands. Trent surprises Mathews with the length as he bangs this one short. It is close to the body but down the leg side. Mathews goes for the pull but ends up getting a fat edge to the left of the keeper. BJ Watling moves to his left and puts a half dive to take a good catch. New Zealand needed early wickets and they have got their first one of the day.
Excellent ball to welcome a new batsman. No one likes to face a yorker first up but Perera had to do just that. Kusal does well to dig it out.
Fuller on off, Kusal looks to drive but it goes off the bottom edge towards mid off.
On the pads, Perera looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.

OUT! LBW! Second wicket in the over for Trent Boult. Kusal has completely misread that one and that has outdone him. Boult steams in and bowls it on a length on off. Kusal expects it to move away and hence he shoulders arms to this one. The ball though comes in and hits the back leg of Perera. New Zealand players put in a huge appeal and the umpire agrees. Perera and Dimuth have a discussion and they opt against the review. Good decision as that looked plumb to the naked eye. Hawk Eye shows that Kusal Perera would have had to continue his walk as the ball was going onto clip the stumps. But one cannot leave such ball on a sub-continental wicket as the ball does not bounce here as much as other countries.
Hits the deck hard on off, Silva defends it to get through the over. An excellent over from Boult. He has jolted the Sri Lankan batting lineup here.
NO BALL! Colin de Grandhomme oversteps! On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off, Dimuth shoulders arms to this one.

OHH! That was not far away from finding the outside edge. Full ball outside off, Karunaratne gets tempted to go for the drive. He goes for it but luckily for him the ball just about misses the outside edge of the Sri Lankan skipper's bat.
Outside off, Dimuth calms his nerves and leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Dimuth lets the ball go outside his off stump.
On the pads, Dimuth flicks it but cannot go past mid-wicket.
On the pads, Dhananjaya flicks it to the on side and gets off the mark.
Fuller on the pads, Karunaratne glances it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Length ball around off, Dhananjaya punches it to cover.

UPPISH AND FOUR! Good length ball on off and middle, the ball sticks onto the surface. Dhananjaya goes for the drive but does so uppishly. It goes wide to the right of Boult. He stretches his right arm out but cannot get close to the ball. The ball races away through mid on for a boundary.
Follows the nervy boundary with a calm front foot defense.
Hits the deck hard on top of the stumps. De Silva blocks it to get through the over.
Length ball around off, Dimuth defends it calmly off his front foot.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Outside off on a length, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Length ball around off, Dimuth punches it to point.
Fuller on middle, Karunaratne pushes it to mid on.
Another maiden from Colin de Grandhomme. The last ball is full on middle and off, Dimuth flicks it to mid-wicket.
On top of off, Dhananjaya defends it with a straight bat towards mid on.
Full ball on off, de Silva strokes it to mid on.
Fuller around off, Dhananjaya looks to drive it on the up but it goes towards square leg off the inner half of his bat.
Good length ball outside off, de Silva shoulders arms to it.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good length ball on off, Silva keeps it out.
Close! Full outside off, Dimuth goes for the drive but misses. The ball was not far away from his outside edge.
Outside off on a length, Karunaratne comes down the track and then leaves it alone.
No ball! Third one from Colin de Grandhomme. He bowls it full on off, Karunaratne defends it off his front foot.
Good length delivery on off, Dimuth plays it to point.
On middle, DK flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Short ball on off, Dimuth pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.

EDGED AND FOUR! Unlucky for the bowler and you have to feel sorry for him. It is a very good ball. Full and swinging in around off, Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the drive but gets a thick inside edge. The ball just about misses the leg pole and races away to the fine leg fence. De Silva was unable to find the gaps but this time he has found one in an unlikely way.
On the pads, Karunaratne flicks it to the on side and gives the strike to Dhananjaya.
Play and miss. Fuller outside off, de Silva goes for the drive but misses.
Fuller on off, Dhananjaya drives it off the inner half of his bat towards mid on.

IN THE AIR...AND DROPPED! Boult cannot blame anyone else as he is the culprit himself. Everyone is shocked as Boult is one of the best fielders going around and he has put down a sitter. Back of a length ball on off, Dhananjaya goes for the flick but ends up getting a leading edge. He ends up ballooning it to side of the pitch on the leg side. Boult calls for it as the fielder from extra cover also comes in. Trent looks to take it with his fingers pointing towards the sky. It looks like an easy catch but Boult fumbles and puts down a sitter. Everyone is stunned!
Outside off, Dhananjaya goes for the drive but misses.
Full ball on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot to get through the over he shouldn't have got through. 1 run off the over, should have had one wicket as well!
On a good length and outside off, Karunaratne offers no shot.
Full and outside off, the skipper drives it to mid off.
Good length delivery outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Full on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Karunaratne shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne looks to defend but gets a leading edge. It goes towards point. The batsmen cross ends.
On the pads, Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Dimuth looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pads towards the leg side for a leg bye.
Short ball around off, de Silva pulls it towards mid-wicket for one.
The batsman has punched that ball through the off side.

Brilliant from Latham! Full on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket. Tom Latham runs in from deep mid-wicket and pulls it back before the ropes with a dive, saving a run in the process. With this 3, Karunaratne completes 12,000 runs in First Class cricket.
Short around off, de Silva pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
On the fourth stump line, de Silva has nothing to do with it and leaves it alone.
Fuller on middle, de Silva flicks it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Full on middle, Karunaratne pushes it to mid on.
Once again de Grandhomme serves it full on off, Dimuth drives it towards mid on as the bat turns in his hand.
Dimuth plants his front foot out and defends it classically.
On the fourth stump line, Dimuth shoulders arms to it to get to Drinks without any further damage.
Starts with a full ball on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, de Silva defends it off the back foot.
Full on off, de Silva gets on his front foot and defends it.
Pulls his length back and bowls it on off, de Silva punches it to cover for one.
Outside off, Karunaratne watches it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, it comes back in. Karunaratne goes for the flick but misses. The ball hits him high on his thigh pad and hence no appeal.
FOUR! Third boundary for Dhananjaya de Silva. A rare loose delivery from Colin. He strays this down the leg side, Dhananjaya just flicks it with ease through fine leg for a boundary.
De Grandhomme corrects his line and bowls it full on off. De Silva defends it off the front foot.
Another full ball on the stumps, Dhananjaya keeps it out.
Pulls his length back and serves it on off, Dhananjaya punches it to cover-point for a run.
Outside off, tempting Dimuth to drive. Karunaratne is having none of it and leaves it alone.
Once again  leaves the ball that is away from the stumps.
Bouncer around off, de Silva hops and pulls it towards mid-wicket. It falls in no man's land. The batsmen take a couple as the fielder from the deep mops it up.
Full on off, de Silva defends it back to the bowler.
Length delivery on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Short now, de Silva pulls it in a controlled manner towards deep mid-wicket for two.
Fuller on off, de Silva defends it off the outer half of his bat towards point.
Non swinging ball outside off, de Silva leaves it alone.

DROPPED! Had Williamson taken that, it would have been a blinder. Tossed up around off, Karunartane comes down the track and flicks it uppishly to the right of short mid-wicket. Kane Williamson there stretches and gets his hands on the ball but he fails to bask it in. Would have been an absolute stunner had he held onto it.
Fighted outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but the ball spins in and hits him on the pad outside off. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Tossed up on off, DK blocks it.
Short and quick around off, Karunaratne looks to play it late but it hits him on the thigh pad.
Once again Diimuth comes down the track but this time he strokes it to cover for one.
Shorter on off, this one spins in to the right-hander. De Silva taps it towards third man against the spin for a single.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne taps it towards point for a single.
Full and outside off, Dhananjaya drives it towards mid off for a quick single.
Good length delivery on off, Dimuth blocks it off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Karunaratne drives it through covers. The batsmen take a run.
Outside off, Dhananjaya lets it go.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya defends it out.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth comes down the track and takes it as a full toss. Karunaratne milks it to long on for one.
Flighted on off, de Silva keeps it out.

Inside edge to the rescue. Tossed up on off, de Silva prods forward to defend but the ball spins in and hits the pad. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Replays later on confirm there was a thick inside edge.
Short and spinning away, de Silva waits and defends it late under his eyes.
Floats one on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Flighted on off, de Silva blocks it to get through the over.
Outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.

OUT! Edged and taken! Massive wicket for New Zealand. It is the Sri Lankan skipper and their best batter, Dimuth Karunaratne. Full ball outside off, Dimuth has been leaving those but on occasions when he has gone for the drive he has missed and been lucky but this time Lady Luck has evaded him. He goes for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge which goes to the left of the wicketkeeper. BJ Watling moves across to that side and takes a simple catch. End of a fabulous innings from the skipper. He will be gutted not to get another century.
Very full outside off, Dickwella initially looks to go after it but then leaves it alone.
On the fifth stump line, Dickwella shoulders arms to it.

OUT! Caught! Second wicket in the over for Southee. Just like Boult did earlier in the day, Southee too has turned the game in just one over. Fuller delivery pitching on off, the ball tails away after hitting the deck. Dickwella goes for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge straight to the keeper. Watling makes no mistake. Dickwella walks without troubling the scorers. Sri Lanka lose wickets in cluster once again. By the looks of it another middle order collapse looks on the cards.
Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and plays it to mid off.
Flighted delivery on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya comes forward and drives it towards mid off for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Perera defends it out.
Loopy delivery outside off, Perera looks to defend but misses it.
TOP EDGE AND FOUR! Short ball on middle and off, Dhananjaya goes for the pull but gets a top edge which flies fine down the leg side. It is in no man's land and goes away to the fence.
Short again, this one does not rise onto the batsman. De Silva pulls it to mid-wicket.
Fuller on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length ball on off, de Silva pulls it towards mid-wicket for one.
Beauty! Full on off, drives the batsman forward to defend. The ball then tails away and beats the batsman comprehensively.

Excellent fielding! It is the skipper, Kane Williamson. Fuller on off, Perera looks to defend but it finds the outside edge and goes to the left of backward point. Williamson there dives to that side and saves runs for his side. 100 marks for the effort.
Peach! Ajaz bowls it slower through the air on off, de Silva looks to defend but the ball spins and grips away and beats the outside edge all ends up.
Floated on off, de Silva defends it off the front foot this time.
Flights one on off, Dhananjaya keeps it out.
On the pads, Dhananjaya flicks it to square leg.
Floated on off, Silva looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
On the stumps, Dhananjaya keeps it out to get through the over.
Bouncer! It is closer to the body, Perera ducks under it.
Fuller on off, Dilruwan keeps it out.
On the stumps, Dilruwan does well to block that away.
Two bouncers sandwiched between two full balls. This is smart bowling. It is around off, DP sits under it.
Back of a length ball around the body, Perera looks to defend but the ball hits him on flush on the glove and then onto his thigh pad.
Length delivery outside off, Dilruwan runs it down to backward point and gets off the mark. He shall keep the strike too.
Flighted on off, Dilruwan defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on middle, Perera strokes it to mid on.
Flights one on off, Perera drives it nicely but straight to the man at cover.
Floated on the stumps, Perera plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
Shorter on off, Dilruwan punches it to cover.
Flighted on off, DP does well to defend it and fight out another over.
Short ball on off, Dhananjaya pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket for one.
Good length delivery on middle, Perera defends it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Perera drives it through mid on. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Bowls a bouncer, Dilruwan does well to duck under it.
Bowls a bouncer again, Perera ducks underneath it.
On a good length and outside off, Perera leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and strokes it to long off for one.
Flighted on off, Perera keeps it out.
Tossed up and spinning away. It pitches on middle and off, Dilruwan looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. Perera played it with soft hands and hence it falls short of the man at first slip.
Flights one on off, Perera keeps it out.
On the pads, Dilruwan flicks it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
On off, Dilruwan keeps it out.
Shorter on off, de Silva punches it to the off side for one.
Good length ball on off, Perera defends it with a straight bat.
Very well bowled short one. It is around off, Perera hops and keeps his bat hanging. Unluckily for Southee, Dilruwan does not glove it.
On the pads, Perera flicks it to square leg.
Very well defended. It is short on the body, Perera hops and does well to keep it out.
Good length ball outside off, DP leaves it alone.
Starts with a shorter ball on leg, Dhananjaya makes room and strokes it to cover point.
Another one short on off, de Silva defends it with the spin towards cover.
Tossed up on off. First one that is full. Dhananjaya bends and keeps it out.
Flights one on off, de Silva cautiously keeps it out.
Floated on the pads, de Silva defends it with a straight bat.
Maiden to start the day. Ajaz gives this one air and bowls it on off, Dhananjaya looks to defend but gets beaten comprehensively by the spin.
Bouncer! Boult starts with a bouncer. It is around the body, Dilruwan ducks under it.
Back of a length on off, Perera gets on his back foot and defends it with calmness.

FOUR! First runs of the day. After two short balls, Boult bowls one fuller on off, Dilruwan looks to defend but the ball goes off the outer half of his bat through the vacant gully region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Dilruwan defends it with the outer half once again.
Back of a length once again. Perera hops and keeps it down.
Bouncer! The over ends the way it started. It is around the body, Perera ducks under it to get through the over.
Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya defends it towards point.
Shorter on off, de Silva blocks it away.
Flighted on middle and off, Dhananjaya looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Floated on off, de Silva defends it properly onto the ground.
Ajaz bowls it short, de Silva defends it to mid off.

FOUR! Nicely played! Brings up the 150 for Sri Lanka. Slightly wide and touch short outside off. Dhananjaya waits and then runs it down to third man with the spin through the vacant third man region for a boundary. The timing on that shot was pure. First runs for de Silva today.
Good length ball on the pads, Perera flicks it wide of short leg, towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Another one around the pads, Dilruwan glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Length ball outside off, de Silva leaves it alone.
On the pads, de Silva glances it to square leg for one.
Fuller on off, Dilruwan pushes it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, DP defends it to get through one more over.
Good intentions from Dhananjaya. Tossed up ball on middle, de Silva comes down the track and hits it hard but straight to mid on.
Follows it up with a calm front foot defense.
Flighted on off, de Silva strokes it to mid off.
Shorter on off, de Silva gets on his back foot and keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, de Silva comes down the track and strokes it to mid off.

FOUR! Excellent shot! Sri Lanka have been too defensive in their approach but this shot was like breaking that chain here. Floated on off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and lofts it over covers for a boundary.
Bowls a bouncer on leg, Perera does well to duck under it.
Boult again bowls a bouncer, Perera ducks underneath it.
Good length delivery on off, Dilruwan defends it to mid off.
Full toss on off, Dilruwan drives it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Perera keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Perera defends it out.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya makes room and guides it towards third man for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Dhananjaya de Silva. Short delivery on off, de Silva cuts it hard through point for a boundary.

FIFTY FOR DHANANJAYA DE SILVA! His 6th in Test cricket. This has been a very fine knock from the young lad. He got a life early on, when Boult dropped him and he has made the full use of it. Shorter on off, de Silva punches it towards point and gets to the other end to get to his milestone.
Flighted on off, Dilruwan defends it off the front foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short with very little spin on offer. Perera defends it with ease.
Now swing first up for Southee. He bangs the first one slightly shorter on off, de Silva punches it to cover.
On a good length on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Outside off, Dhananjaya shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya taps it to point.
On a length on off, Dhananjaya defends it out.
Flighted on off, Dilruwan defends it off the front foot.
Darts one on the pads, Dilruwan glances it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Short and spinning away. De Silva punches it towards cover for a single.
Shorter on off, Dilruwan defends it with the spin towards cover.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is and Dilruwan has to walk back. Excellent ball this! Short and quick on off, Dilruwan expects it to spin and so he goes onto his back foot to play it on the off side. The ball though keeps straight and skids of the surface. Perera misses his shot and gets hit on the pad. Huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Dilruwan has a chat with Dhananjaya. After a brief chat, he opts to take it upstairs. Replays roll in and Hawk Eye shows that the ball would have gone on to clip the stumps. Dilruwan walks back but does not take the review with him. First wicket for Ajaz in this game.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lakmal has come out with an aggressive approach here. Shorter around off, Lakmal throws his bat at it. The ball takes the outside edge and flies wide of the diving second slip to the third man fence for a boundary. Lakmal starts his innings with a Strike Rate of 400.
On a good length on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Southee bowls it short on middle, Dhananjaya pulls it through square leg for a boundary. This is good batting from Dhananjaya de Silva.
Short and outside off, de Silva cuts it through point for a run.
On a good length on off, Lakmal defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a short delivery outside off, Lakmal looks to fend at  it but misses it.
Short delivery, Lakmal looks to pull but gets a top edge. The ball goes towards third man who is very fine. They do not take the run as Dhananjaya wants to keep the strike.
Tossed up on middle, Dhananjaya defends it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Tossed up on middle, Dhananjaya plays a slog sweep over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Dhananjaya taps it towards point for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Lakmal defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! Tossed up just outside off, Lakmal looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Good length ball on off, Dhananjaya shuffles across and turns it to fine leg for a single.

In the air but safe. Excellent bowling this. A very well directed short ball this. It is right around the body. Lakmal looks to defend but takes his eyes off. The ball lobs well short of the keeper. Watling comes running in but had no chance. It would not have mattered had he even got there as replay shows the ball had hit Suranga around his shoulder.

Another brilliant short ball. This is just a tad away from the body. Lakmal looks to defend but once again takes his eyes off the ball. This time though the ball does not hit him and goes to the keeper.
Hat-trick of short balls. This is played well by Lakmal. It is around the body,  Suranga this time keeps his eyes on the ball and sways away from it.
Back of a length ball on the body, Suranga tucks it wide of short leg.
Another ball on the body. It is on a length, Lakmal turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Flighted on middle, Lakmal glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a brace.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal taps it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle and leg, Lakmal bends his back and keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Suranga nudges it towards cover for one.

FOUR! Smart batting! Flighted delivery on off and middle, de Silva gets down on one knee and paddles it fine down the leg side. Taylor predicts it and runs to the leg side from first slip but he cannot stop the ball from beating him and going to the fence.
Floated on off, de Silva pushes it to cover.

In the air but in no man's land. Back of a length ball on the body, Lakmal clears his front foot and looks to hoick his pull. He ends up top edging. Watling and the fielder from deep mid-wicket come running in but the ball falls far away from them, right in between. Single taken.
On the pads, Silva glances it towards short fine leg.
Very full on off, de Silva keeps it out.
Short ball on middle and leg, de Silva pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Bouncer! Lakmal reads it early and sits under it.
Yorker on middle, Lakmal does really well to get his bat down in time.
Fuller on middle, this one tails in a bit. Dhananjaya defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on the pads, Dhananjaya flicks it towards deep mid-wicket and surprisingly refuses to take a single.
On the pads, de Silva once again flicks and does not take the single.

Nicley played. Fuller outside off, Dhananjaya gets on his front foot and drives it wide of sweeper cover. This time they run as there is two easily available. Jeet Raval in the deep runs to his right and puts in a dive to save a boundary. He is successful in his mission and saves two for his side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Lady Luck is with Dhananjaya de Silva here. Full ball outside off, de Silva looks to play it on the off side but ends up getting a big inside edge. The ball misses the stumps and goes to the fine leg fence for a boundary. Any other day that might have gone on to chop the stumps but not today.

Smart batting this. Dhananjaya has taken upon himself here. He plays the first 5 balls of the innings and then takes the single of the last one. It is full on off, Dhananjaya strokes it towards mid off and takes a quick single to keep the strike with himself.
No swing on this one as it goes straight to the keeper outside off.
Good length ball outside off, this one shapes away a bit. Dhananjaya leaves it alone.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Full and swinging away. Dhananjaya drives it but straight to cover.

Another good looking stroke and this time de Silva takes a single. Full outside off, Dhananjaya drives it through cover-point. There is a fielder in the deep so just one. Lakmal has two balls to fight here.
Gets through the first one easily. Good length ball outside off, shapes away a little. Lakmal lets it go to the keeper.
Negotiates the second one too. Full on off, Lakmal glances it towards deep mid-wicket but de Silva does not take the single.

Lovely shot! Full on off, Dhananjaya gets on his front foot and drives it through covers. The outfield is a bit slow today and hence the ball does not have the legs to go to the fence. They take two as the fielder cleans it up.
Well bowled. Good length ball outside off, this one shapes in. De Silva looks to defend but gets beaten all ends up.
Back of a length ball on off, de Silva keeps it out.
On the pads, de Silva tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On top of off, de Silva defends it with a straight bat towards mid off.

IN THE AIR AND JUST OVER! SIX! Short ball on middle and leg, Dhananjaya picks the length early, gets on his back foot and hooks it over fine leg. William Somerville in the deep is just inside the ropes. He jumps and stretches but the ball just goes over for a maximum.
Swing and a miss. Full outside off, Lakmal swings his bat at it as he wants to clear the park. He does not connect though.
Full on middle and leg, Lakmal flicks it to square leg for one.

Very full on middle. Just a few inches away from being a yorker. Dhananjaya glances it towards deep square leg for a single. De Silva is confident to give strike to Lakmal, as he feels Suranga can face Southee.
Ouch! Short ball on off, Lakmal hops and looks to defend. The ball kisses the outside edge and once again hits the bruised arm of Lakmal. We will have slight delay.

OUT! Caught! The short ball has done the trick. Excellent catch from Watling. Good aggression from Southee. He bangs another one short around the body. Lakmal looks to defend but ends up gloving it to the right of Watling. BJ was wrong footed but he corrects himself and dives on that side and takes a very good catch. The 43-run stand is broken. A crucial stand this and one must credit Lakmal for his fight. He made the Kiwis toil hard for his wicket.
Full on off, Embuldeniya shows sound technique as he defends his first ball off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Dhananjaya defends it towards mid off.
Short ball around off, Dhananjaya pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket but does not take any run.

EDGED AND SIX! Into the nervous 90s now. Short ball around the body, Dhananjaya looks to pull but gets a top edge which goes fine down the leg side. It does not look like it will go all the way over the ropes but to the surprise of everyone it does.

EDGED AND FOUR! Moves to 94 now. Good length ball angling away from the right-hander. Dhananjaya looks to defend with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes wide of second slip on a bounce. Southee dives to his right but cannot get to the ball and it races away to the fence.

Full on off, de Silva plays a very handsome straight drive. It goes to the right of mid off. It looks like it will beat the man there but Ajaz Patel dives and deflects the ball to mid on saving a certain boundary.
Good length ball on off, de Silva punches it to cover. 10 off the over.

OUT! LBW! The ball is clipping the leg pole and Embuldeniya has to walk back. 4-fer for Southee. Good length ball pitching on middle. It comes back in after pitching, Lasith looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his front pad. A confident appeal follows and the umpire gives Lasith Embuldeniya his marching orders. He takes a desperate review. Replay first confirms no involvement of bat. Hawk Eye later on rolls and shows all red and Embuldeniya has to walk back.
Survives the first one. Good length ball on off, Kumara does well to defend it.
Another one seen off. Dhananjaya will be a lot happy. Fuller on off, Kumara gets his bat down and keeps it out
Bouncer! Lahiru ducks under it and lets it carry to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Kumara keeps it out.
Attempted yorker, but comes out as a full toss on off. Lahiru does well to guide it to point.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

FOUR! Excellent shot but credit to Ajaz for his effort. Length ball on middle and off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and lofts it over mid off. It looks a certain boundary but Ajaz comes running in from long off and puts in a very good dive. It looks clean but Ajaz straightaway signals a boundary. The umpires still have a look and it shows his feet touched the ropes when he palmed it away. Full marks for the effort and honesty there for Ajaz. Dhananjaya moves to 98 now.
Back of a length ball on off, de Silva defends it off his back foot.
On the body,  Silva tucks it to the on side.
Good length ball on off, de Silva punches it towards cover. Can he sneak out a single here or even get to his 100? Surely he would not want Kumara to face the new over.
He does manage to get the single. Poor ball this as it is on the pads, de Silva flicks it to fine leg for single.
Fuller on off, de Silva pushes it to mid off.
Almost chopped on. Good length ball closer to the off pole, Dhananjaya looks to play a risky late cut. He gets an inside edge and luckily it goes to the keeper and not onto the stumps.
Full on off, de Silva drives it straight to cover.

FOUR! 100 FOR DHANANJAYA DE SILVA! Take a bow, son! This has been a fabulous knock. He has made Boult pay for his mistake and single-handedly kept his side in the hunt. Fuller on off, Dhananjaya lofts it over covers and gets a boundary which gets him to his 5th Test hundred. He raises his bat, removes his helmet, lifts it and soaks in all the applause.
Yorker on middle, de Silva does well to glance it to the leg side for a single.
Hang on a minute, Lahiru showing his skills with the willow here. Full on middle, Kumara lofts it over the bowler's head and gets a couple as the fielder from long on mops it up.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya looks to pull but gets a bottom edge on this one.
Short delivery on middle, Dhananjaya pulls it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, de Silva tucks it to the leg side.
On a length on off, Dhananjaya guides it towards third man.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Trent Boult. Bowls a full toss on off, Dhananjaya smashes it through covers for a boundary.
Short delivery on middle, Dhananjaya pulls it to mid-wicket. He does not take the single.
Back of a length ball on off, Kumara defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Kumara strokes it towards cover for a single.
Bouncer on off, Dhananjaya pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Short ball on middle and leg, Kumara takes his eyes off the ball and awkwardly keeps it out with a flat bat.
Short again outside off, Lahiru swings his bat to pull but misses.
Full around off, Lahiru lofts it over cover. The man at cover jumps and stretches his hand out but cannot get close to it. The fielder from long off cleans it as the batsmen come back for the second.
Length delivery on off, Dhananjaya taps it to point.

OUT! Bowled! End of a fabulous knock. Slower ball on a length, Dhananjaya swings his bat at it. He was going for a big heave but misses. The ball crashes onto the middle stump. Maybe that was the indication from the skipper from the dressing room and hence this shot came out. SRI LANKA ALL OUT FOR 244.
Starts with a flatter delivery on off, Jeet Raval does well to defend it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Raval blocks it off his front foot this time.
Flighted on leg and middle, Raval once again defends it off the front foot.
Oh! Quicker on off, Raval looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The Sri Lankan players are buzzing here.
Arm ball outside off, Raval leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Jeet keeps it out of his back foot to get through the first over unscathed.
Starts with a flighted delivery on off, Latham calmly begins his innings with a front foot defense.
Tossed up outside off, Tom reads the spin properly and leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Latham defends it off his back foot this time.
New Zealand are underway! Floated on the pads, Latham glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Floated on off, Jeet gets on his front foot and defends it onto the ground.
Tossed up on off, Raval blocks it away to get to Lunch on Day 3.
Starts with a good length ball outside off. No swing on this one, Latham shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, Latham flicks but finds square leg. He shouts a loud 'wait on' to his partner.
Very good leave this from Latham. Length ball just outside the off stump. Latham is aware of his off stump and leaves it alone.
Comes 'round the wicket and bowls it full on off. Latham defends it towards mid on with the angle.
On the 4th stump line, Latham is in no mood to tease those.
Full and angling in on off. Latham pushes it to mid off. Maiden to start the new session.

OUT! Caught! Early blow for New Zealand. Jeet Raval goes out without troubling the scorers. Flighted delivery on off, it is an off spinner and slower through the air. Raval misreads this as he lunges forward to defend. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to first slip. Dhananjaya de Silva there takes a simple catch. A good welcome back to national fold for Dilruwan.
Floated on middle and leg, Williamson glances it to mid-wicket.
Skipper Kane is off the mark. Flighted delivery on the pads, Williamson glances it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Flatter outside off, Latham was looking to play the premeditated sweep shot but then looking at the length he retracts from it.
Short on the pads, Latham flicks it wide of short leg, towards square leg for one.

Nicely played. Short off spinner pitching on off. Williamson gets on his back foot and punches it with the spin through covers for a couple. Mathews there has a little chase with the ball. Two taken by the Kiwi captain.
Good length ball outside off, Latham shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Latham shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length delivery on middle, Williamson flicks it to square leg.
Full on middle, Williamson drives it to mid on where the fielder does well to stop it with a dive.
Good length delivery outside off, Kane lets it go.
Floated very full on middle, Latham paddles it fine down the leg side for a brace.
Flatter outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Latham prods forward to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Shorter on off, Latham punches it to the off side for a run.
FOUR! Poor ball and rightfully punished. It is short on the body from Dilruwan. Williamson transfers the weight onto his back foot and swipes it away through square leg for a boundary.
Under edge to the rescue. Once again it is short but this is not as short as the previous one. It is on middle and leg, Williamson once again looks to pull it but gets a slight edge onto his pad.
Good length ball on middle, Latham turns it behind square on the leg side for a couple.
Fuller outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery on off, Tom defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Tom punches it towards cover for one.
On top of middle, Williamson defends it straight back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Signature shot from Williamson. Fuller ball around off, Williamson plays it very late in his trademark style and taps it through the third man region for a boundary. Williamson loves that region. That shot was like a sweet poetry, always a delight.
FOUR! Two boundaries in a row for New Zealand. It is short and Latham is quick to pounce on it. Short around off, Latham gets on his back foot and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated on off, Latham follows the boundary with a calm front foot defense.
Floats one outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Arm ball on the pads, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket.

Appeal for an LBW but nothing from the umpire. Dilruwan bowls it flatter and quicker on off. It goes with the angle, Latham looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal from the Sri Lankan players but nothing from the umpire. It looked to be going down leg. Hawk Eye later on rolls in and shows that the ball was clipping the leg pole. Would have stayed with the on-field umpire's decision.
Floated outside off, TL does not tease that.
Fuller on middle, Williamson glances it towards square leg for a single.
Beauty! Lakmal hits the deck hard around off, asking the batter to have a poke at it. The ball zips away from Tom and just misses his outside edge.
Good length ball on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Another play and miss! Bowls it on a length around off, Latham looks to defend but the ball nips away and squares Latham all ends up.
Length ball on off, Tom defends it off the back foot.
Fuller on off, Latham blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Williamson defends it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Williamson drives it through covers. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Floated delivery on middle, Williamson flicks it towards short leg.
Loopy delivery on middle, Williamson defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Kane flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.
The ball is way outside the off stump, easy leave for the batsman.

Huge appeal from the keeper but nothing from the bowler. Good length ball outside off, Williamson looks to play it late towards the third man region. He misses and the ball goes very closely past the outside edge towards the keeper. Dickwella goes up in a confident appeal but Lahiru does not join in. The umpire too is not interested.
On the pads, Williamson flicks it to the on side and gets a single.
Good length ball on off, Tom keeps it out.
Back of a length ball on off, Latham defends it off his back foot.
Down the leg side. Latham looks to flick but misses.
Floated on off, Williamson looks to defend but gets a bottom edge onto the pads.
Floated on the pads, Williamson flicks it to the on side for a single.
Flights one on off, Williamson blocks it off the front foot.
On the off pole, Williamson lunges forward and keeps it out.
On the pads, Williamson glances it to square leg for  one.
Flighted on off, Latham blocks it onto the ground.
Full on off, Williamson strokes it to mid off.
Full around off, Williamson plays a very good looking cover drive. Dhananjaya de Silva there does not gather it cleanly and that allows them to take a run.
On the pads, Latham glances it fine down the leg side for a run.
Full on off, Latham drives it straight through mid on for a couple.

OUT! Caught! Williamson departs against the run of play here. Big blow for the Kiwis. Good length ball outside off, Williamson tries to play his trademark tap towards the third man region. He ends up hitting it straight to second slip who was just a tad wide. Kusal Mendis there takes a very good catch. Smart captaincy this from Karunaratne to just keep that slip wide as that is Williamson's go-to region. Sri Lanka on top here.
Taylor is off the mark. Length ball around off, Taylor strokes it to point and keeps the strike.
Floated outside off, Taylor looks to drive but with very minimal footwork. It goes off the inner half of his bat towards the on side.
Flighted on off, Taylor taps it back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Taylor blocks it off the front foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up on the stumps, Ross gets on his front foot and keeps it out.
Tossed up on the pads, Ross looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards square leg for a run.
On a length on off, Taylor taps it towards point for a run.
Full on middle, Latham flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Taylor looks to drive but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Taylor shoulders arms to this one.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Taylor looks to cut but misses it.
BEATEN! Tossed up just outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses it due to the turn on this one.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle, Latham keeps it out.
NOT OUT! Flighted delivery on off, Latham looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Hawk Eye shows that it is missing the off stump.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up on middle, Latham defends it out.
On a good length on off, Taylor blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Taylor shoulders arms to this one.
Short of a length delivery, Taylor pulls it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
FOUR! On a good length and outside off, Latham looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Latham defends it out.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery. Tossed up on off, Taylor looks to defend but misses the outside edge by a whisker.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor sweeps it to the leg side.
Floated delivery on off, Taylor drives it through covers for a run.
Tossed up on middle, Latham plays it towards point for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor comes down the track and plays it towards mid on for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Latham punches it towards point for a run.
On a good length and outside off, Latham taps it towards the off side and takes a quick run.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Taylor flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
On a good length on off, Taylor keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Latham blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Latham nudges it towards square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor keeps it out.
FOUR! Nice shot. Flighted delivery outside off, Taylor sweeps it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Starts with a flighted delivery outside off, Latham premeditates his paddle sweep and takes a single as the ball goes behind square on the leg side.
Loopy ball on middle, Taylor strokes it to mid on.
Down the leg side, Taylor sweeps it fine down the leg side for a run.
Play and miss. Slower through the air on off, Latham looks to defend but the ball spins away and squares Latham up.
Flights it around off, it comes as a full toss. Latham sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for one.
On the pads, Taylor glances it to the on side for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham flicks it to the leg side.
Tossed up on off, Latham plays it to point.
Tossed up on off, Latham looks to cut but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man. The batsmen get three runs.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on off, Latham comes down the track and plays it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up on off, Taylor drives it to mid off.
FOUR! Good shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor comes down the track and drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Taylor drives it to mid off.
Loopy delivery on off, Taylor drives it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor punches it to point.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Latham drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Latham looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full on off, Latham drives it to covers.
Loopy delivery on off, Latham punches it towards point for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham comes down the track and blocks it well.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham sweeps it to square leg.
Tossed up on off, Taylor keeps it out.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Flighted delivery on off, Taylor drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, Taylor leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor blocks it off the front foot.
Floated on off, Latham prods forward and strokes it to cover for one.
Arm ball on the pads, Taylor tucks it to short leg.
On the pads, Ross flicks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Glorious! Latham brings up the 50-run stand in style. Flighted delivery on off, Latham gets on his front foot and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Another good drive but straight to mid off.
Short around off, Latham punches it to mid off to get through the over. Just in case you are wondering why the last ball took so long, it is because there was a miscalculation.
Flighted on off, Ross pushes it to mid off.

OUT! Caught! Deja vu moment for Ross Taylor. Just like in the second innings in Galle, Taylor once again loses his patience and throws it away. Flighted around off, Taylor comes down the track making it seem like he was tired of the defensive game. He does not get to the pitch of the ball but he is so far in front that he has to go and play at it. Taylor only manages to get a thick outside edge straight to first slip. Dhananjaya de Silva just cannot do anything wrong today and he takes another catch. Unnecessary shot at this stage, it was just not needed.
Floated on  off, Nicholls sweeps it hard. The ball hits short leg and goes past him towards square leg for a single.

FOUR! Latham carries his good work. Flighted on off, Latham comes down the track and slams it through mid on for a boundary. Suranga Lakmal stationed at long on chases it but he is casual in his approach and the ball beats him to the fence comprehensively.
Flights one on off, Latham keeps it out.
Tossed up outside off, Tom gets down on one knee and looks to sweep but misses.
Tossed up away from the off pole, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Flighted on the stumps, Nicholls keeps it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Nicholls plants his front foot forward and once again calmly blocks it.
Shorter on off, Nicholls gets on his back foot and defends it.
Tossed up on off, Nicholls keeps it out to get through the over.
Darts one down the leg side, Latham looks to flick but misses.
Floated on off, Tom comes down the track and keeps it out.
Floats one on off, Latham once again comes down and blocks it.
Flights one outside off, Tom goes for a big sweep but misses.
Tom is in no hurry and he confidently keeps this out off his front foot.
On the pads, Latham glances it towards square leg and keeps the strike.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls defends it out.
Tossed up on leg, Latham sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham comes down the track and drives it to long on for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls punches it towards mid on for a run.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR TOM LATHAM! This has been a fine knock from him and till now he's been the sole fighter for the Kiwis. Tom has kept losing wickets from the other end but he has held his own here. He gets to his 16th fifty in stylish fashion too. Flighted delivery on off, Latham gets down on one knee and sweeps it through the square leg region for a boundary. Subdued celebrations from him as he knows the job is not done yet. He will now look to convert this into a big one.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls flicks it towards mid-wicket where the ball falls just short of the fielder.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham plays a sweep through square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up on off, Nicholls keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Henry defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls defends it out.
Tossed up on leg, Latham looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham defends it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls defends it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Nicholls plays it towards point for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham defends it off the front foot. THAT IS TEA ON DAY 3!
Starts with a full ball around off, Nicholls drives it but not of the middle and straight to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Henry pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Good length ball on off, Tom keeps it out off his front foot.
Back of a length on off, Latham defends it with a straight bat.
Bouncer! It is on off, Tom ducks under it.
Full again on off, Latham taps it back to the bowler to get through the over.
Floated on off, Nicholls keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Nicholls gets on his front foot and defends it.
On the pads, Henry flicks it towards square leg and gets to the other end.
Floats one on middle, Latham gets on his front foot and blocks it onto the ground.
Loops this on middle, Latham comes down the track and nudges it to long on to get to the other end.
On the pads, Nicholls flicks it but gets hit on the pads.
Good length ball on off, TL milks it to cover for one.
Bouncer outside off, Henry sways away from it.
Fuller on the stumps, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
On top of off, Nicholls stands tall and punches it wide of deep point. They run the first one hard and challenge the fielder as they call for the second. They get it with ease.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Nicholls pushes it to cover.
Flighted on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Tom comes down the track and milks it to mid off.
Shorter and spinning in, Latham gets on his back foot and flat bats it wide of extra cover for one.
Short again, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, Nicholls glances it to square leg.
Tossed up on the stumps, Nicholls keeps it out to get through the over.
In the air but in no man's land. Back of a length ball on off and middle. Latham looks to pull but gets a top edge which falls  in no man's land at square leg. Single taken.
Nicholls shows Latham how to pull with confidence and ease as he pulls this one towards deep mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Tom leaves it alone.
Length delivery around off, Tom runs it down to third man and gets a couple.
Fuller on middle and off, Tom strokes it to mid on.
Very good fielding from Oshada! Full around off, Latham, drives it to the right of cover. Oshada Fernando at short cover dives to  his right and saves runs for his side. A single taken.

Appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Floated delivery around off, Latham gets down on one knee and tries to sweep. He misses and the ball hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They do not take the review as Perera feels it is missing off. Good decision as the Hawk Eye later on confirms that to be true.
FOUR! Pummeled away. Short around off, Tom picks it early. He goes on his back foot and flat bats it over mid on for a boundary.
Shorter on off, Tom punches it to cover.
Flighted on off, Latham blocks it off his front foot.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On the pads, Latham looks to flick but misses and the ball hits him high on the thigh pad.
Around middle, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Very well played. A short ball, outside off, Nicholls plays a controlled pull shot through mid-wicket past the fielder inside the circle for a run. He kept that all along the ground.
Outside off, played through point for a run.
Full and outside off, driven back to the bowler.
A bouncer but down the leg side, Tom ducks.
Another wayward bouncer, ducked under again.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it to short leg.
Floated delivery on middle, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery, Nicholls plays a controlled pull through square leg for a run.
On a good length on middle, Latham tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Latham plays it towards point for a single.
Length delivery on off, Nicholls defends it to covers.
On a length on middle, Nicholls tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length and outside off, Nicholls punches it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
Short and spinning away. Nicholls gets on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Flighted on off, Henry defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! Caught! The budding partnership has been broken. Seems like the rain break got a bit of discrepancy in Nicholls' concentration. Slower through the air on off, Nicholls has a push at it. The ball though turns away and kisses the outside edge of the bat. It goes to the right of first slip and once again it is Dhananjaya de Silva who takes the catch. Third catch of this innings for him to follow up the big ton.
Floated on off, Watling starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Tossed up around off, Watling keeps it out.
Watling gets off the mark. Tossed up on off, Watling strokes it to cover and keeps the strike.

FOUR! Unlucky for the bowler. Kumara steams in and bowls a 145 kph ball full on off and middle. The ball moves away at the last minute. Watling looks to play it straight but the ball goes off the outside edge through the gully region for a boundary.
This time flicks it off the middle towards mid-wicket for a single.
Wide! Bouncer bounces too high. It is over the head of Latham who sits under it.
On the pads, Tom flicks it wide of fine leg for a couple.
Full on middle and off, Latham defends it towards point and shouts a loud wait.
On off, Latham pushes it to mid off.
Good leave. Length delivery outside off, it comes back in. Tom though is aware of his off stump and leaves it alone.
