Almost a catch there! Loose from Dickwella. He chases a short ball outside off and tries to guide it down towards third man. But it takes the outside edge and flies behind. Ross Taylor at short third man dives across to his right and parries it towards the fielder at short fine leg. A single taken.
FOUR! Fine shot! Too full in length on off, Lakmal drives it through covers and the ball races away to the fence in no time.
Loopy off spinner on off, Lakmal leans to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated full ball on off, Dickwella is on the front foot in defense.
Bowls this one with a round-arm action and delivers it short on off, Dickwella defends it from the back foot.
On the pads, nudged to short fine leg.
A bit short in length outside off, Dickwella cuts it to point.
Quicker and on off, blocked off the back foot by Niroshan.
Nicely tossed up ball on off, Dickwella skips down the track and defends it back. Maiden. Lakmal will be now exposed for the entire next over.
Big spin down the leg side, a patient leave made by Suranga Lakmal.
Flatter and shorter outside off, punched from the back foot to covers.
Spinning down leg from around off, Suranga tries to flick but misses and is hit on the pads.
Floated and full on middle, Lakmal presses forward to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to covers.

Shout for a caught behind! The umpire is not convinced. Lovely drift on this delivery, it  lands on off and turns in with some extra bounce. Lakmal lunges to defend but misses and Watling collects it over the stumps. A late appeal from the bowler but nothing doing. This was a similar delivery on which Kusal Mendis got bowled.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery. Another maiden!
Patel switches to over the wicket and bowls a flatter full ball on off, Niroshan defends it off his front foot.
Flighted and outside off, defended to the off side.
Allows the ball to spin back in and then defends it down wide of short leg.
Tossed up ball on off, turning in, Dickwella is on the front foot as he defends it near his front pad.
FOUR! Well played! Flighted delivery, landing full on off, Niroshan advances down the track and just pushes it gently over mid off for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on off, Niroshan strides forward and defends.
Floated around the pads, the ball hits his pad and then  the arms.
Tossed up on leg, Lakmal looks to defend but it lobs of the edge wide off forward short leg.
This time defends it off the middle.
FOUR! Short on the body, Lakmal gets on his back foot and pulls it through the vacant mid-wicket region for a boundary. Sri Lankan supporters starting to find their voice here.
Follows it up with a calm defense.
SIX! High and handsome. Tossed up on middle and leg, Lakmal picks the length early and smashes it over the long on fence for a biggie. He is not shying away from swinging his bat.
Floated on off, Dickwella gets on his back foot and defends it.
On the pads, Niroshan defends it to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Dickwella turns it against the spin towards square leg for one.
Very full on middle and off, Lakmal keeps it out.
Proper leave this as this one pitches around off and spins away.
Tossed up around off, Lakmal defends it off the outer half of his bat towards point.
FOUR! Superbly played! Loopy and full, landing outside off, Dickwella sweeps it against the spin but backs it with great power. A boundary at mid-wicket results.
Loopy delivery, wide outside off, an easy leave for Niroshan.
Floated one, pitching full on off, Dickwella paddle sweeps it towards fine leg for one.
Fuller in length on off, it's driven back to the bowler.
Off spinner landing full on middle, Lakmal offers no shot and takes it on the pads.
Very full in length on middle and leg, Lakmal defends it in front of forward short leg.
Good length delivery in the zone outside off, Niroshan has nothing to do with it.
Angles in a length ball on middle, Dickwella defends it off his back foot to the leg side.
Pitches it up and outside off, it's pushed in the gap at covers and Dickwella denies the single.
Boult switches to 'round the wicket and hurls in a bouncer around middle, Dickwella crouches and sways away from the line of fire.
Identical to the last delivery, further angling away from the left-hander, Niroshan drops his wrists and lets it be.
Waste of energy and ball. Bouncer well outside off, Dickwella makes another leave to close the over.
Flighted off spinner on off, turning in with extra bounce, Lakmal tries to defend but misses.
A touch short and outside off, Lakmal moves inside the crease and defends it off the inner half to the leg side.

OUT! Lakmal's fight is over! Somerville strikes to break this 107-ball partnership! A superbly tossed up off spinner. It hits the deck outside off and breaks back in to kiss the gloves of Lakmal who was trying to defend. It then brushes his pads and lobs to Latham at forward short leg. He takes the simplest of catches and Sri Lanka lose their eighth wicket. The Kiwis are relieved. 25.3 overs left in the Test match to pick the remaining two wickets.
Embuldeniya has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Quicker and flatter close to off, Embuldeniya tries to defend but it goes past the outside edge.
Loopy and outside off, Lasith allows it through. A wicket maiden for Somerville!
Back of a length ball on off, Dickwella defends it off his back foot.
Beaten! Angling away from the batsman around off, Dickwella pushes inside the line and misses.
Back of a length ball on middle, Dickwella stands back and dead bats it down the surface.
On and around off, a length ball, it's solidly blocked by Niroshan.

13th Test fifty for Niroshan Dickwella! He is not too excited about this fifty as he knows that his job is only half done. Short delivery around middle, Niroshan rides the bounce and eases his pull shot down to fine leg for a run.
Boult serves it on a length and outside off, it keeps its line after pitching, Embuldeniya plays inside the line and lets it go.
Loopy and landing full outside off, spinning away, Dickwella allows it through.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it with the spin to the off side.
Floated and on off, Dickwella gets down and paddles it fine down the leg side for a run. 3 balls for Embuldeniya to survive.
Well tossed up off spinner, pitching full on off, Lasith defends it confidently to the off side.
Fires it in, full and on off, straightening a bit after landing, Embuldeniya gets forward to defend with firm hands. It falls in front of silly point.
Tossed up ball on off, Lasith defends it watchfully to survive the over. 23 more overs left in the day, don't think we will get that far with the light fading.
Angles in a length ball on off, Dickwella defends it near his front pad.
Goes fuller and darts it on off, Dickwella defends it to mid off.
Hurls in an inswinger outside off, Dickwella shoulders arms.
Back of a length ball on off, Niroshan defends it from the back foot to covers.

Leading edge but safe! Boult spears in a very full ball on leg, Dickwella tries to flick but gets a big leading edge. Fortunately for Sri Lanka it goes wide of Taylor at covers. Good stop by the veteran with a dive.
Fullish and on off, it's pushed off the front foot to covers. New Zealand have achieved their objective. It will be Lasith Embuldeniya on strike in the next over.
Beats the bat straightaway! Flighted and full outside off, not turning much, Embuldeniya tries to defend but misses.
Too full in length on off, Lasith brings his bat down and digs it out off the outer half to third man. A single taken. Not ideal for New Zealand.

OUT! What have you done Dickwella? Pensive faces in the Sri Lankan dressing room. Ajaz serves a flighted full ball around off, Dickwella gets down to play the paddle sweep but there is some extra bounce and it takes the top half of his bat before deflecting from the arm-guard. The ball loops in the air and Latham moves across to his left in anticipation from forward short leg to grab a fine reflex catch. Dickwella is frustrated with himself. New Zealand celebrate. They can smell a win here, only 1 wicket more left to pick.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
FOUR! Very full in length and sliding down the leg side, Embuldeniya gets bat on ball and flicks it behind square leg for a boundary.

OUT! Embuldeniya is bounced out! NEW ZEALAND WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 65 RUNS! A snorter by Boult. He digs in a well-directed short ball on middle and Embuldeniya is caught by surprise. He takes his eyes off the ball, tries to fend at it but the ball takes his gloves and balloons to Williamson at gully. The Kiwi skipper does the rest and it's a convincing win for the Black Caps to level the 2-match series.
